nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glycine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets glycine through ten interconnected prebiotic routes spanning hydrothermal carbon fixation, surface cyanide and carbonyl chemistry, and biochemical/prebiotic conversion steps. The network is built around hub intermediates shared across environments: carbon dioxide, formate, formaldehyde, hydrogen cyanide, glyoxylate, and glycine itself. Hydrothermal reactions generate reduced C1-C3 feedstocks such as formate, acetate, pyruvate, formaldehyde, and glycolaldehyde on iron-sulfur and iron-oxide minerals. Surface environments use these feedstocks in HCN photochemistry, Strecker-type synthesis, formose/aldol chemistry, and oxidation to glyoxylate. Biochemical/prebiotic steps connect \u03b1-keto acid and aminonitrile chemistry to the final amino acid pool and peptide-forming context. The resulting bipartite graph provides multiple convergent and redundant routes to glycine while preserving full network connectivity and cross-environment transfer.\n\nMOLECULES (18 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H2O3 (glyoxylic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H3NO2 (glycine) [target]\n  - mol_012: C2H2N2 (cyanogen) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: CHNO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C2H2N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: CH2N2 (methanimine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C2H4N2O (glycinenitrile amide / aminocyanoformamide analogue) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (22 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Hydrothermal reduction of carbon dioxide to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal conversion of formate to formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_008 (Hydrothermal Fischer-Tropsch-type formation of glycolaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_009 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from CO2 and H2) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_009, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_018 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_006, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical generation of HCN from reduced C1 feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_004 -> mol_013 (Surface HCN hydration to formamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_004, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Surface partial hydrolysis/reduction of HCN to methanimine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_006, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_014 (Surface Strecker synthesis of aminoacetonitrile from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_015, mol_004 -> mol_014 (Surface aminoacetonitrile formation from methanimine and HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_008 -> mol_010 (Surface oxidation of glycolaldehyde to glyoxylate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_009 -> mol_010 (Surface oxidative fragmentation of pyruvate to glyoxylate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_013: mol_006, mol_008 -> mol_016 (Surface borate-stabilized formose step to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_016 -> mol_010, mol_006 (Surface retro-aldol/oxidative conversion of glyceraldehyde to glyoxylate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_015: mol_004 -> mol_012 (Surface HCN dimerization to cyanogen) [Surface]\n  - rxn_016: mol_012, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_014 (Surface conversion of cyanogen and ammonia to aminoacetonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_017: mol_013, mol_004 -> mol_017 (Surface formamide-cyanide route to aminoacetonitrile derivative) [Surface]\n  - rxn_018: mol_017 -> mol_011 (Surface hydrolytic conversion of activated glycine nitrile-amide to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_019: mol_014 -> mol_011 (Surface hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_020: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Surface reductive amination of glyoxylate to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_021: mol_010, mol_018 -> mol_011, mol_009 (Biochemical/prebiotic transamination of glyoxylate to glycine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_022: mol_009, mol_003 -> mol_011 (Biochemical decarboxylation/oxidative shortening of pyruvate to glycine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Canonical Strecker route from hydrothermal formaldehyde (5 steps)\n  - P2: Direct formaldehyde Strecker without explicit HCN regeneration loop (4 steps)\n  - P3: Methanimine-mediated aminonitrile route (4 steps)\n  - P4: Cyanogen branch to aminoacetonitrile (4 steps)\n  - P5: Formamide-derived nitrile-amide route (4 steps)\n  - P6: Hydrothermal glycolaldehyde to surface glyoxylate to glycine (3 steps)\n  - P7: Hydrothermal pyruvate to surface glyoxylate to glycine (3 steps)\n  - P8: Borate-stabilized sugar route to glyoxylate and glycine (5 steps)\n  - P9: Hydrothermal alanine to biochemical transamination route (4 steps)\n  - P10: Proto-metabolic shortening of pyruvate to glycine (2 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_006, mol_009, mol_010, mol_014\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if con