nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glycine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets glycine by emphasizing chemically better-supported prebiotic routes and avoiding previously flagged weak steps such as direct formaldehyde-to-HCN generation, cyanogen-based aminoacetonitrile formation, pyruvate shortening to glycine, and underspecified pyruvate-to-glyoxylate fragmentation. The network uses externally plausible simple feedstocks (CO2, H2, NH3, HCN, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, phosphate, water) and connects three environments. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies reduced C1/C2 and keto-acid intermediates such as formate, acetate, pyruvate, and acetaldehyde on iron-sulfur and iron-oxide minerals. Surface chemistry uses HCN, aldehydes, borate-stabilized sugar chemistry, UV/TiO2 photochemistry, and phosphate minerals to generate aminoacetonitrile, glycolonitrile, glycolaldehyde, glyceraldehyde, glyoxylate, and glycine. Biochemical/prebiotic chemistry then converts hydrothermal and surface intermediates through hydrolysis, reductive amination analogs, transamination, and peptide assembly. Ten pathways are represented as distinct valid routes to glycine, with strongest convergence at aminoacetonitrile, glycolonitrile, glyoxylate, and formaldehyde.\n\nMOLECULES (19 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CHOO- (formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H3O2- (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H3O3- (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C2HO3- (glyoxylate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [target]\n  - mol_016: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: H3PO4 (phosphate) [starting]\n  - mol_018: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_019: C4H8N2O3 (glycylglycine) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (18 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002, mol_006 -> mol_007 (Hydrothermal acetate formation from CO2-derived C1 units) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_007, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_008 (Hydrothermal pyruvate synthesis from acetate and CO2) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_008, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_016 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_008 -> mol_009, mol_001 (Hydrothermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005 -> mol_010 (Surface formaldehyde dimerization to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_010, mol_005 -> mol_011 (Surface aldol extension of glycolaldehyde to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_004, mol_005 -> mol_012 (Surface HCN addition to formaldehyde forming glycolonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_005, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_013 (Surface Strecker formation of aminoacetonitrile from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_012, mol_003 -> mol_013 (Surface ammonolysis of glycolonitrile to aminoacetonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_012, mol_018 -> mol_010, mol_004 (Surface hydrolysis of glycolonitrile to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_010 -> mol_014 (Surface oxidation of glycolaldehyde to glyoxylate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_013: mol_011 -> mol_014, mol_005 (Surface oxidation of glyceraldehyde to glyoxylate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_013, mol_018 -> mol_015 (Biochemical hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_015: mol_012, mol_003, mol_018 -> mol_015 (Biochemical hydrolysis of glycolonitrile to glycine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_016: mol_014, mol_016 -> mol_015, mol_008 (Biochemical transamination of glyoxylate to glycine using alanine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_017: mol_014, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Biochemical reductive amination analog of glyoxylate to glycine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_018: mol_015 -> mol_019 (Biochemical wet-dry condensation of glycine to glycylglycine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Canonical Strecker route from external formaldehyde (2 steps)\n  - P2: Cyanohydrin-first route from formaldehyde (3 steps)\n  - P3: Direct glycolonitrile-to-glycine route (2 steps)\n  - P4: Formaldehyde to glycolaldehyde to glyoxylate to glycine (3 steps)\n  - P5: Sugar-extension route to glyoxylate then glycine (4 steps)\n  - P6: Hydrothermal pyruvate to alanine to glycine transamination route (4 steps)\n  - P7: Hydrothermal acetate to pyruvate branch feeding transamination (6 steps)\n  - P8: Hydrothermal pyruvate-decaboxylation branch to glyoxylate chemistry (5 steps)\n  - P9: Reversible cyanohydrin loop reinforcing Strecker glycine synthesis (4 steps)\n  - P10: Hydrothermal-to-surface-to-biochemical integrated route (6 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_005, mol_008, mol_013, mol_014\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pa